The paper focuses on the performance analysis of distributed algorithms for blockchain systems, which involves aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC), cryptography (cs.CR), and networking (cs.NI). The analysis also involves measuring latency and network usage, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the classification of protocols as permissioned or permissionless, which relates to system and control theory (cs.SY).
